The paper proposes a machine learning approach using convolutional neural networks to analyse cardiotocography time series signals for the early detection of abnormal birth outcomes. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically involves feature extraction (cs.CE) and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of machine learning for medical diagnosis also falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves image analysis using convolutional neural networks (cs.CV) to analyse the time series signals.
